description: For sale: $350,000. Gorgeous 3BR/2BA in highly sought after St. Louis Park neighborhood! This home has tons of original character with cove ceilings, picture rail & original oak floors, as well as numerous custom upgrades throughout. Step into spacious main floor living room with wood burning fireplace. Formal dining room with sight-lines to kitchen & french doors to back deck/yard, perfect for entertaining. Kitchen boasts granite, full-height cabinets, SS appliances & gas range. Side door from kitchen leads leads to backyard/patio perfect for summer cookouts. Two bedrooms w/ custom shiplap ceilings & full bath w/custom tile work round out the main level. Upper level includes impressive master suite w/ seating area & walkthrough closet. Meticulously finished LL includes rec room/home theater, office, 3/4 bathroom & laundry/utility space w/ original workbench. Home located in quiet neighborhood near all of the conveniences of SLP & easy access to HWY 100 & just minutes to downtown MPLS.

description: For sale: $1,149,000. As the old real estate saying goes - location, location, location. This nearly one acre setting in South Tyrol is one of the most sought after in the Twin Cities. In addition to its convenient location, this 6600+ sq ft home has been completely remodeled and transformed to a modern-day soft contemporary. Excellent attention to detail. One of the most distinctive features of the home is the master suite, with fireplace and a large outdoor deck. There is a spiral stair case that leads to the lower level and your private indoor pool, hot tub, sauna as well as a work-out room. You have all the amenities of premium hotel right off your master bedroom. Car buff? Enjoy your heated four stall+ garage. The home has been a great hang-out for all featuring an arcade, a theater room, and of course the pool. Just 3 miles to downtown Minneapolis. Walk to the West End and Wirth Park.

description: For sale: $339,900. This condo is unique and incredibly exciting! Flex space! Note the over-sized rooms. The den can be used as a sleeping room, office for 2, currently shown as a formal dining room.  The living room can house a piano or a pool table (think first floor) in addition to your couch and GIANT screen TV. The 17' long bedroom can easily accommodate a desk or exercise equipment and a king bed. A huge ensuite bath shares a dressing room lined with high end closet organizers on 2 walls.  A niche in the large foyer can be used for storage and will safely display your bicycle!  High ceilings with knock down finish, cherry floors that flow through out and abundant cherry cabinetry in the large kitchen showcase the quality. Built as a "loft", a RayDoor sliding wall system steals the show in quiet fingertip ease of operation and superior craftsmanship. Enjoy first floor ease of access from the private entrance and fenced patio. LOVE the 25' of floor to ceiling S facing glass! This is the 1 and only!

For sale: $1,000,000. Stunning home overlooking the park! This showstopper had an expansive remodel in 1991. Designed and built with a 2x6  passive solar design for energy efficiency and also has many smart home features. Beautiful preserved cove ceilings, hardwood floors with a cozy fireplace in the living room. Large, updated kitchen with Subzero refrigerator, updated 5 burner gas cook top, exhaust range hood, & dishwasher. Main floor family room with gas fireplace, lighted wood tray ceilings, smart draperies!  The 5th bedroom "Princess tower" is a feature you won't want to miss!  Wonderful home office space with a fireplace and its own entrance. A nice feature if meeting clients at home. Outside perennial gardens embedded in stone retaining walls will bring various blooms of color. Just minutes from downtown MPLS, Theodore Wirth Park, Benilde, Breck and Blake! Easy access to 100 and 394. Love where you live!

description: For sale: $450,000. Minikahda Oakes English Tudor cottage style home.  The main level features spacious living and dining rooms, an eat-in kitchen, three bedrooms, and a full bath. A lovely home in a lovely neighborhood by Bass Lake Park and close to shopping, restaurants, and transit.

description: Recently sold: $254,500. Charming 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom apartment that features lots of great maple cabinetry and flooring to go along with a large, open living area overlooking a huge green space and lots of walking and biking trails. This main floor unit gives you the flexibility of just walking out your patio door to hit the trails, no need to walk through the building. Wonderful granite countertops and great storage. Huge master bedroom! This building shares amenities such as a pool, work out room, sauna, hot tub and party room with the 3705 building. These are exquisite buildings in a fantastic location walking distance to lakes, restaurants, grocery and entertainment. Convenient! This is one you will need to put on your list!

Recently sold: $975,000. Exceptional Morningside Farm House style home built in 2006. Walk to a variety of popular dining & coffee shop options, boutiques, grocery store, Golden Years Montessori, parks and more located within just a few blocks. Less than a mile from Linden Hills and 50th and France. Charming front porch will welcome family & friends. Spacious main level open floor plan. Brazilian cherry floors, enameled center island granite & stainless high end kitchen. Lovely stone fireplace flanked by built-ins and south facing transom windows. Private first floor flex room. Recently updated powder room. Fantastic mud room & walk-in closet. Back staircase leads to four bedrooms & spacious laundry room up. Romantic master suite/ retreat includes master bath with separate walk-in shower. Huge walk-in closet. Walkout to private deck and stunning, professionally landscaped private backyard. Unfinished basement is framed in and provides an opportunity to create future living space. Two large egress windows.

description: Recently sold: $369,300. Welcome to the "Honeymoon Cottage". Built by an architect as a gift for his bride, this storybook Cape Cod home has been totally updated throughout. Freshly painted with today?s colors, the interior of the home features original hardwood floors which have been newly refinished and enameled millwork. Enjoy a spacious Family Room, a Dining Room with original built-in china cabinets, two remodeled Bathrooms and a remodeled Kitchen with stainless steel appliances. In addition to the two main floor Bedrooms, the upper level Bedroom features fir hardwood floors and a charming dormer. The driveway was crafted with repurposed brick from behind the Minneapolis Post Office and leads to the detached 3 Car Garage where you will find a Workshop and over 400 fsf of heated space above that could be a Home Office or Studio. Beautifully landscaped, the setting is surrounded by hostas, mature trees and colorful flowers. Walk or bike to multiple nearby parks to picnic or spend an afternoon at Lake Harriet, Lake Calhoun or Lake of the Isles! Located on a quiet street in the wonderful Creekside community, this closely-knit neighborhood enjoys easy access to 50th & France, dining, shopping, schools and golf courses.
